OL,4,CJulie Burchill makes 'full' apology for
OL,5,Cracist abuse of fellow writer
OL,6, Writer and columnist Julie Burchill has
OL,7, issued a 600-word "unreserved" apology
OL,8, and agreed to pay substantial damages
OL,9, after a two-week campaign of abuse
OL,10, against journalist Ash Sarkar.
OL,12,FIn December, Burchill accused Ms Sarkar
OL,13,Fon Twitter of condoning paedophilia
OL,14,Fworshipping the Prophet Muhammad and
OL,15,Fsupporting Islamist terrorism.
OL,17,FIn her apology, Ms Burchill said: "I
OL,18,Fshould not have sent these tweets, some
OL,19,Fof which included racist and misogynist
OL,20,Fcomments regarding Ms Sarkar's
OL,21,Fappearance and her sex life."
